A chaotic scene unfolded at Glasgow airport as a blazing jeep rammed into the terminal, prompting evacuations and arrests.
British Prime Minister Gordon Brown confirmed the incident as a terrorist attack, leading to heightened security measures.
The attack was linked to foiled car bomb plots in London, emphasizing the need for vigilance.
Two suspects were arrested in connection with the attacks, with one in critical condition.
Security was tightened at airports across Britain, underscoring the government's commitment to public safety.
The incident serves as a stark reminder of the ongoing threat of terrorism.
